---
/**
 * about.astro — "Two Worlds, One Love for Hong Kong"
 * Route: /about
 */
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { Image } from 'astro:assets';
import scottImg from '../../images/scott-murray.jpg';
import jeniceImg from '../../images/jenice-murray.jpg';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About Us — Scott & Jenice"
  description="We're Scott and Jenice — an American with 10+ trips to Hong Kong and a cultural eye for what guidebooks miss. This is our story."
>

<!-- ═══════════════ HERO ═══════════════ -->
<section class="about-hero">
  <video class="about-hero-video" autoplay muted loop playsinline preload="metadata">
    <source src="/videos/pillar/about-hero.mp4" type="video/mp4" />
  </video>
  <div class="about-hero-gradient-overlay"></div>
  <div class="hero-grid"></div>
  <div class="about-hero-inner">
    <div class="hero-eyebrow">About Discovering Hong Kong</div>
    <h1>Two Perspectives, One <em>Hong Kong</em></h1>
    <p class="hero-intro">We're Scott and Jenice — Scott with a logistics obsession that started in 2007 when a friend said "you should visit Hong Kong," and Jenice with the cultural eye that spots the authentic teahouse in a sea of tourist traps. Ten-plus trips across Hong Kong Island, Kowloon, the New Territories, and the Outlying Islands. This is how a city that takes 20 minutes end-to-end on the MTR somehow keeps revealing new layers on every visit.</p>
    <div class="hero-line"></div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ═══════════════ PERSONAL LETTERS ═══════════════ -->
<section class="letter-section reveal">
  <div class="letter-block">
    <div class="letter-attr">Scott <span class="attr-role">· American · First Hong Kong trip: 2007 · 10+ return trips</span></div>
    <p class="letter-text">I first came to Hong Kong in 2007 on a stopover that turned into three days of wandering I still think about. The MTR blew my mind — the cleanliness, the frequency, the way it connected everything. I ate wonton noodles at 7am that cost HKD 38 and tasted better than anything I'd had at a "proper" restaurant. I took the Star Ferry at sunset and understood immediately why people say the Victoria Harbour skyline is one of the great views on Earth.<br><br>I've been back 10+ times since — usually with Jenice, sometimes alone when work takes me through the region. We've hiked Dragon's Back and MacLehose Trail Stage 2. We've found our way to the teahouses in Jordan where the menus are only in Cantonese and the dim sum starts at dawn. We've taken the 12-minute ferry to Lamma Island for seafood and stayed until dark. Each trip adds another layer.<br><br><strong>I'm not a travel blogger. I work in healthcare IT.</strong> But Hong Kong keeps pulling me back, and I finally decided to put everything I've learned into something useful — a site with real prices, an AI trip planner built on actual experience, and video content from the places we've actually been. Not press trips. Not affiliate dumps. Just an honest guide from two people who genuinely love this city.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="letter-block">
    <div class="letter-attr">Jenice <span class="attr-role">· Cultural eye · Food instinct · The one who finds the real spots</span></div>
    <p class="letter-text">Hong Kong has layers that most visitors never reach — not because they're hidden, but because you need to know what you're looking for. I bring the instinct for that. The ability to walk into a restaurant and read the room immediately: who's eating here, what they're ordering, whether the kitchen knows what it's doing.<br><br>The first time we had dim sum in a proper Jordan teahouse — not a tourist restaurant, but a place where the trolleys come out at 6am and the regulars have their table and their tea and their order already known — I understood something about Hong Kong that no guidebook had ever conveyed. This is a city that rewards people who pay attention.<br><br>I look for the egg tart shops without the Instagram queue. The roast goose places where the line of locals tells you everything. The dai pai dong stalls where the plastic stools and the fluorescent lights are features, not bugs. <strong>Scott handles the maps and the logistics. I handle the taste and the instinct.</strong> Together, we want you to experience Hong Kong the way we do — not the surface version, but the real one.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ═══════════════ TIMELINE ═══════════════ -->
<section class="timeline-section">
  <div class="timeline-header">
    <div class="section-eyebrow">Our Story</div>
    <h2 class="section-title">15+ Years in the Making</h2>
  </div>
  <div class="timeline">
    <div class="tl-item reveal">
      <div class="tl-year-side"><div class="tl-year">2007</div></div>
      <div class="tl-dot"></div>
      <div class="tl-content-side"><div class="tl-content">
        <div class="tl-title">The Stopover That Changed Everything</div>
        <p class="tl-text">A three-day stopover on a longer trip. Scott rides the MTR end to end, eats wonton noodles for breakfast, and takes the Star Ferry at sunset. He books a return trip before he leaves the city.</p>
      </div></div>
    </div>
    <div class="tl-item reveal">
      <div class="tl-year-side"><div class="tl-year">2009</div></div>
      <div class="tl-dot"></div>
      <div class="tl-content-side"><div class="tl-content">
        <div class="tl-title">First Proper Exploration</div>
        <p class="tl-text">A week-long trip with no agenda beyond the MTR map. Victoria Peak at dawn, the Lamma Island ferry for seafood, the night markets of Mong Kok. The first time Scott realizes Hong Kong has 200 hiking trails and zero of them get mentioned in typical travel content.</p>
      </div></div>
    </div>
    <div class="tl-item reveal">
      <div class="tl-year-side"><div class="tl-year">2012</div></div>
      <div class="tl-dot"></div>
      <div class="tl-content-side"><div class="tl-content">
        <div class="tl-title">Jenice Joins — The Cultural Shift</div>
        <p class="tl-text">Jenice's first Hong Kong trip transforms the experience. She finds the Jordan teahouse where dim sum starts at 6am and the menu is Cantonese-only. She spots the roast goose queue that locals know and tourists walk past. Every trip since has been different.</p>
      </div></div>
    </div>
    <div class="tl-item reveal">
      <div class="tl-year-side"><div class="tl-year">2015–22</div></div>
      <div class="tl-dot"></div>
      <div class="tl-content-side"><div class="tl-content">
        <div class="tl-title">Deeper Into the City</div>
        <p class="tl-text">Dragon's Back Trail. MacLehose Stage 2. The Outlying Islands. Sai Kung seafood villages. Tai O stilt village. The UNESCO Geopark hexagonal rocks. Scott starts videoing everything — because no travel site is showing what these places actually look and feel like.</p>
      </div></div>
    </div>
    <div class="tl-item reveal">
      <div class="tl-year-side"><div class="tl-year">2025</div></div>
      <div class="tl-dot"></div>
      <div class="tl-content-side"><div class="tl-content">
        <div class="tl-title">Discovering Hong Kong Launches</div>
        <p class="tl-text">The guide Scott wished had existed in 2007 finally becomes real — with video content, an AI trip planner backed by real HKD prices, and Jenice's cultural eye powering every food and cultural recommendation. Not recycled content. A real guide from two people who love this city.</p>
      </div></div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ═══════════════ PROFILE CARDS ═══════════════ -->
<section class="profiles-section">
  <div class="profiles-header">
    <div class="section-eyebrow">Meet the Team</div>
    <h2 class="section-title">The People Behind the Pages</h2>
  </div>
  <div class="profiles-grid">
    <div class="profile-card reveal">
      <div class="profile-banner scott"><div class="profile-banner-bg"></div></div>
      <Image src={scottImg} alt="Scott Murray" class="profile-avatar scott-av" width={96} height={96} format="webp" loading="lazy" />
      <div class="profile-body">
        <div class="profile-name">Scott</div>
        <div class="profile-role">Co-founder · Writer · Videographer · The Logistics Brain</div>
        <p class="profile-bio">Healthcare IT professional by day, Hong Kong travel obsessive by every other waking moment. Based in San Diego, CA. First visited Hong Kong in 2007 on a stopover that turned into a three-day adventure — and sparked 10+ return trips across every district and region. Enjoys the trip planning almost as much as the travel itself. Still convinced there are hiking trails in the New Territories he hasn't found yet.</p>
        <div class="profile-stats">
          <div class="profile-stat"><div class="profile-stat-num">2007</div><div class="profile-stat-label">First HK trip</div></div>
          <div class="profile-stat"><div class="profile-stat-num">10+</div><div class="profile-stat-label">Trips & counting</div></div>
          <div class="profile-stat"><div class="profile-stat-num">40+</div><div class="profile-stat-label">Countries traveled</div></div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="profile-card reveal">
      <div class="profile-banner jenice"><div class="profile-banner-bg"></div></div>
      <Image src={jeniceImg} alt="Jenice Murray" class="profile-avatar jenice-av" width={96} height={96} format="webp" loading="lazy" />
      <div class="profile-body">
        <div class="profile-name">Jenice</div>
        <div class="profile-role">Co-founder · Cultural Eye · Food Expert · The Instinct</div>
        <p class="profile-bio">The person who walks into a restaurant and immediately reads whether it's the real thing or the tourist version. Jenice brings an instinct for authentic local experiences that transforms every Hong Kong trip. She finds the dim sum teahouses where regulars have been sitting at the same table for 30 years, the dai pai dong stalls where the food is worth the plastic stool, and the cultural context that makes Hong Kong's layers visible rather than invisible.</p>
        <div class="profile-stats">
          <div class="profile-stat"><div class="profile-stat-num">10+</div><div class="profile-stat-label">HK trips together</div></div>
          <div class="profile-stat"><div class="profile-stat-num">Dim Sum</div><div class="profile-stat-label">Her specialty</div></div>
          <div class="profile-stat"><div class="profile-stat-num">Local</div><div class="profile-stat-label">Eye always</div></div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ═══════════════ OUR PROMISE ═══════════════ -->
<section class="promise-section">
  <div class="promise-inner">
    <div class="section-eyebrow">Our Promise</div>
    <h2 class="section-title">What You'll Never Find Here</h2>
    <p class="promise-text">We built this site because we got tired of Hong Kong travel content that's either a hotel review dressed up as honest advice or a listicle of places every other site already covers. We want you to experience Hong Kong the way we do — not the Instagram version, but the real one.</p>
    <div class="zero-grid">
      <div class="zero-card reveal"><div class="zero-num coral">0</div><div class="zero-label">Sponsored posts<br><em>ever</em></div></div>
      <div class="zero-card reveal"><div class="zero-num teal">0</div><div class="zero-label">Press trips or<br>free hotel stays</div></div>
      <div class="zero-card reveal"><div class="zero-num gold">10+</div><div class="zero-label">Return trips to<br>Hong Kong</div></div>
      <div class="zero-card reveal"><div class="zero-num white-num">100%</div><div class="zero-label">Real prices in<br>HKD & USD</div></div>
    </div>
    <div class="promise-quote">If we recommend it, we've been there. If we list a price, we've paid it. If we tell you to skip something, we've wasted our own money there first.</div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ═══════════════ WHAT WE'RE BUILDING ═══════════════ -->
<section class="vision-section">
  <div class="vision-inner">
    <div class="vision-content">
      <div class="section-eyebrow">What We're Building</div>
      <h2 class="section-title">More Than a Travel Blog</h2>
      <p class="vision-text">Discovering Hong Kong isn't a collection of "Top 10" listicles. It's a living resource built on 10+ trips of real experience, cultural expertise, and technology that actually helps you plan a better trip.</p>
      <ul class="vision-list">
        <li><span class="v-icon">🎥</span> Video guides for select destinations — see the harbour, markets, and trails before you book</li>
        <li><span class="v-icon">🤖</span> An AI trip planner that builds custom itineraries with real HKD prices, not guesses</li>
        <li><span class="v-icon">💰</span> Every price listed in both HKD and USD, updated based on what we actually pay</li>
        <li><span class="v-icon">👥</span> Cultural context from Jenice — the instinct for what's authentic versus what's tourist bait</li>
      </ul>
      <div class="btn-row">
        <a href="/plan/" class="btn-primary">✦ Try the AI Trip Planner</a>
        <a href="/destinations/" class="btn-outline">Browse All Destinations</a>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="vision-features">
      <a href="/destinations/" class="v-feature reveal"><div class="v-feature-icon">🏙️</div><div class="v-feature-title">Destination Guides</div><div class="v-feature-desc">Deep dives into each district — not surface-level overviews, but neighborhood-level detail with real logistics and HKD prices.</div></a>
      <div class="v-feature reveal"><div class="v-feature-icon">📹</div><div class="v-feature-title">Video Content</div><div class="v-feature-desc">Real footage from Mong Kok, Sai Kung, Lantau Island, the Star Ferry, and the hiking trails — see it before you go.</div></div>
      <a href="/plan/" class="v-feature reveal"><div class="v-feature-icon">🗺️</div><div class="v-feature-title">AI Trip Planner</div><div class="v-feature-desc">Describe your dream Hong Kong trip and get a custom day-by-day itinerary built on real experience and HKD prices.</div></a>
      <div class="v-feature reveal"><div class="v-feature-icon">📧</div><div class="v-feature-title">Itinerary Downloads</div><div class="v-feature-desc">PDF itineraries you can take offline — complete with MTR routing, booking links, and insider tips from Jenice.</div></div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ═══════════════ EMAIL CTA ═══════════════ -->
<section class="email-cta-section">
  <div class="email-cta-inner">
    <h2 class="section-title">Get the Guide Before Everyone Else</h2>
    <p class="email-cta-desc">We're building new destination guides, video content, and trip planner features every month. Drop your email and we'll send the good stuff first — no spam, no affiliate dumps, just real Hong Kong travel intel from two people who actually go there.</p>
    <form class="email-form" onsubmit="event.preventDefault();">
      <input type="email" class="email-input" placeholder="your@email.com" />
      <button type="submit" class="btn-sand">Subscribe &rarr;</button>
    </form>
    <p class="email-note">We respect your inbox. Unsubscribe anytime.</p>
  </div>
</section>

</BaseLayout>

<script>
  if (!window.matchMedia('(prefers-reduced-motion: reduce)').matches) {
    const ro = new IntersectionObserver(entries => {
      entries.forEach(e => { if (e.isIntersecting) e.target.classList.add('visible'); });
    }, { threshold: 0.1, rootMargin: '0px 0px -40px 0px' });
    document.querySelectorAll('.reveal').forEach(el => ro.observe(el));
  } else {
    document.querySelectorAll('.reveal').forEach(el => el.classList.add('visible'));
  }
</script>

<style>
  .about-hero {
    padding: 160px 24px 100px;
    position: relative;
    overflow: hidden;
    text-align: center;
    background: linear-gradient(165deg, #141C26 0%, #172830 30%, #1a3035 55%, #172830 75%, #141C26 100%);
  }
  .about-hero-video {
    position: absolute;
    inset: 0;
    width: 100%;
    height: 100%;
    object-fit: cover;
    z-index: 0;
  }
  .about-hero-gradient-overlay {
    position: absolute;
    inset: 0;
    background: linear-gradient(to bottom, rgba(0,0,0,0.1) 0%, rgba(0,0,0,0.15) 40%, rgba(0,0,0,0.55) 100%);
    z-index: 0;
  }
  .hero-grid {
    position: absolute;
    inset: 0;
    pointer-events: none;
    background-image:
      linear-gradient(rgba(255,255,255,0.012) 1px, transparent 1px),
      linear-gradient(90deg, rgba(255,255,255,0.012) 1px, transparent 1px);
    background-size: 60px 60px;
  }
  .about-hero-inner {
    max-width: 760px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    position: relative;
    z-index: 2;
  }
  .hero-eyebrow {
    font-size: 0.68rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: 0.22em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--color-warm-gold);
    margin-bottom: 24px;
    opacity: 0;
    animation: heroUp 1s cubic-bezier(0.16,1,0.3,1) forwards 0.2s;
  }
  .about-hero h1 {
    font-family: var(--font-serif);
    font-size: clamp(2.2rem, 5.5vw, 3.8rem);
    color: white;
    line-height: 1.1;
    margin-bottom: 28px;
    opacity: 0;
    animation: heroUp 1s cubic-bezier(0.16,1,0.3,1) forwards 0.4s;
  }
  .about-hero h1 em {
    color: var(--color-warm-gold);
    font-style: italic;
  }
  .hero-intro {
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    color: rgba(255,255,255,0.65);
    line-height: 1.85;
    font-weight: 300;
    max-width: 620px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    opacity: 0;
    animation: heroUp 1s cubic-bezier(0.16,1,0.3,1) forwards 0.6s;
  }
  .hero-line {
    width: 1px;
    height: 56px;
    margin: 48px auto 0;
    background: linear-gradient(to bottom, rgba(212,165,116,0.5), transparent);
    opacity: 0;
    animation: heroUp 1s cubic-bezier(0.16,1,0.3,1) forwards 0.9s;
  }
  @keyframes heroUp {
    from { opacity: 0; transform: translateY(28px); }
    to { opacity: 1; transform: translateY(0); }
  }

  .letter-section {
    padding: 80px 24px 64px;
    max-width: var(--content-lg);
    margin: 0 auto;
  }
  .letter-block {
    position: relative;
    padding-left: 32px;
    border-left: 2px solid #EBE4D8;
    margin-bottom: 52px;
    transition: border-color 0.5s ease;
  }
  .letter-block:hover { border-left-color: var(--color-ocean-teal); }
  .letter-block:last-child { margin-bottom: 0; }
  .letter-attr {
    font-size: 0.7rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: 0.12em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--color-warm-coral);
    margin-bottom: 14px;
  }
  .letter-attr .attr-role {
    color: #718096;
    font-weight: 400;
    letter-spacing: 0.05em;
  }
  .letter-text {
    font-size: 1.02rem;
    line-height: 2;
    color: var(--color-deep-night);
    font-weight: 300;
  }
  .letter-text strong { font-weight: 600; }

  .timeline-section {
    padding: 80px 24px 100px;
    background: var(--color-white);
  }
  .timeline-header {
    text-align: center;
    max-width: var(--content-lg);
    margin: 0 auto 72px;
  }
  .section-eyebrow {
    font-size: 0.66rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: 0.2em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--color-warm-coral);
    margin-bottom: 12px;
  }
  .section-title {
    font-family: var(--font-serif);
    font-size: clamp(1.8rem, 4vw, 2.4rem);
    color: var(--color-deep-night);
    line-height: 1.15;
  }
  .timeline {
    max-width: var(--max-width, 1120px);
    margin: 0 auto;
    position: relative;
  }
  .timeline::before {
    content: '';
    position: absolute;
    left: 50%;
    top: 0;
    bottom: 0;
    width: 2px;
    transform: translateX(-50%);
    background: linear-gradient(to bottom, #EBE4D8, var(--color-ocean-teal), var(--color-warm-coral), var(--color-warm-gold), #EBE4D8);
  }
  .tl-item {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 60px;
    margin-bottom: 64px;
    position: relative;
    align-items: center;
  }
  .tl-item:last-child { margin-bottom: 0; }
  .tl-dot {
    position: absolute;
    left: 50%;
    top: 50%;
    transform: translate(-50%, -50%);
    width: 14px;
    height: 14px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    background: var(--color-white);
    border: 3px solid var(--color-ocean-teal);
    z-index: 2;
    transition: all 0.3s ease;
  }
  .tl-item:hover .tl-dot {
    background: var(--color-warm-coral);
    border-color: var(--color-warm-coral);
    transform: translate(-50%, -50%) scale(1.35);
    box-shadow: 0 0 0 6px rgba(232,101,74,0.15);
  }
  .tl-year {
    font-family: var(--font-serif);
    font-size: 3.5rem;
    color: #EBE4D8;
    line-height: 1;
    transition: color 0.5s ease;
  }
  .tl-item:hover .tl-year { color: var(--color-ocean-teal); }
  .tl-content { max-width: 420px; }
  .tl-title {
    font-family: var(--font-serif);
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    color: var(--color-deep-night);
    margin-bottom: 10px;
  }
  .tl-text {
    font-size: 0.88rem;
    color: var(--color-slate);
    line-height: 1.8;
    font-weight: 300;
  }
  .tl-item:nth-child(odd) .tl-year-side { text-align: right; }
  .tl-item:nth-child(odd) .tl-content-side { text-align: left; padding-left: 12px; }
  .tl-item:nth-child(even) { direction: rtl; }
  .tl-item:nth-child(even) > * { direction: ltr; }
  .tl-item:nth-child(even) .tl-year-side { text-align: right; }
  .tl-item:nth-child(even) .tl-content-side { text-align: left; padding-left: 12px; }

  .profiles-section {
    padding: 100px 24px;
    background: var(--color-sand);
  }
  .profiles-header {
    text-align: center;
    max-width: var(--content-lg);
    margin: 0 auto 56px;
  }
  .profiles-grid {
    max-width: var(--max-width, 1120px);
    margin: 0 auto;
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 40px;
  }
  .profile-card {
    background: var(--color-white);
    border-radius: 24px;
    overflow: hidden;
    box-shadow: 0 4px 24px rgba(26,35,50,0.08);
    transition: transform 0.4s cubic-bezier(0.4,0,0.2,1), box-shadow 0.4s cubic-bezier(0.4,0,0.2,1);
  }
  .profile-card:hover {
    transform: translateY(-8px);
    box-shadow: 0 12px 48px rgba(26,35,50,0.14);
  }
  .profile-banner { height: 200px; position: relative; overflow: hidden; }
  .profile-banner-bg { position: absolute; inset: 0; transition: transform 0.8s ease; }
  .profile-card:hover .profile-banner-bg { transform: scale(1.08); }
  .profile-banner.scott {
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, #0c3547 0%, #0D7377 40%, #14B8A6 70%, #38D9A9 100%);
  }
  .profile-banner.jenice {
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, #78350F 0%, #D4A574 40%, #FBBF24 70%, #FDE68A 100%);
  }
  .profile-banner::after {
    content: '';
    position: absolute;
    inset: 0;
    pointer-events: none;
    background-image:
      radial-gradient(circle 80px at 25% 35%, rgba(255,255,255,0.06), transparent),
      radial-gradient(circle 60px at 75% 65%, rgba(255,255,255,0.04), transparent);
  }
  .profile-avatar {
    width: 96px;
    height: 96px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    border: 4px solid var(--color-white);
    margin: -48px auto 0;
    position: relative;
    z-index: 2;
    object-fit: cover;
    box-shadow: 0 4px 20px rgba(0,0,0,0.12);
    transition: transform 0.3s ease;
  }
  .profile-card:hover .profile-avatar { transform: scale(1.08); }
  .profile-avatar.scott-av { background: linear-gradient(135deg, #0D7377, #14B8A6); }
  .profile-avatar.jenice-av { background: linear-gradient(135deg, #D4A574, #FBBF24); }
  .profile-body { padding: 20px 32px 32px; text-align: center; }
  .profile-name {
    font-family: var(--font-serif);
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    color: var(--color-deep-night);
    margin-bottom: 4px;
  }
  .profile-role {
    font-size: 0.76rem;
    color: #718096;
    font-weight: 400;
    margin-bottom: 20px;
    line-height: 1.5;
  }
  .profile-bio {
    font-size: 0.86rem;
    color: var(--color-slate);
    line-height: 1.85;
